#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rcdb Specifying inputs: configuration dialog boxes #!N 
#!EC #!N #!N To open the configuration dialog box for a 
tool, either: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o 
Double click on the tool icon in the canvas,  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   or 
#!EF #!N #!I30 #!N o Single click on (highlight) the tool 
icon in the canvas and select "Configuration" from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit 
#!EF pull-down menu. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N In the case 
of interactors, color maps, the Image tool, and the Sequencer, the 
first procedure invokes a "control box" (another kind of dialog box). 
The second procedure always invokes a configuration dialog box. #!N #!I0 
#!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Tabs and inputs to a tool 
module #!EF #!I50 #!N Each input parameter in the configuration dialog 
box corresponds to an upper tab on the tool icon. The 
leftmost tab corresponds to the first parameter, and so on. #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Visible versus hidden parameters #!EF #!I50 #!N At 
the bottom of the dialog box are  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Expand #!EF and 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Collapse #!EF buttons. The first button "expands" the dialog box, 
displaying additional parameters. The second button "collapses" the dialog box, hiding 
every parameter whose "Hide" toggle button is activated. (When a tool 
has no hidden parameters, both buttons are disabled, as indicated by 
their gray labels.) #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next 
Topic #!EF #!N #!N  #!Lall30,dxall31 h Specifying inputs: arcs and icons  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
